STEP 1 — Keycloak Setup (DO THIS FIRST)

http://localhost:8080
username: admin
PASSWORD: admin

1. Create Realm
Go to Realm dropdown
Click Create Realm
Name: 

camara-platform

2. Create Client (Partner)
Clients → Create

| Field       | Value          |
| ----------- | -------------- |
| Client ID   | `camara-platform`  |
| Client Type | OpenID Connect |
| Access Type | Confidential   |

Enable Flows

Inside client:
Authentication flow --> ON
✔ Standard Flow (Authorization Code) → ON
✔ Direct Access → ON
OAuth 2.0 Device Authorization Grant
OIDC CIBA Grant
Client authentication --> ON
Authorization--> ON

Get Client Secret

Go to: Credentials tab
Copy:
client_id
client_secret

3. Set Redirect URL

Example: http://localhost:3000/callback

4. Create Scope (API Access)

Go to:  Client Scopes → Create 
Example: nv.verify
nv.read

5. Add Custom Claim (MSISDN Placeholder)

Go to: Client → Mappers → Create

| Field            | Value          |
| ---------------- | -------------- |
| Name             | msisdn         |
| Mapper Type      | User Attribute |
| User Attribute   | msisdn         |
| Token Claim Name | msisdn         |


KONG:

Now test Kong is working.

1. Add Test Service

curl -i -X POST http://localhost:8001/services \
  --data "name=test-service" \
  --data "url=https://httpbin.org"

2. Add Route

curl -i -X POST http://localhost:8001/services/test-service/routes \
  --data "paths[]=/test"

3. Test

curl http://localhost:8000/test/get

If working → Kong is correct ✅


